        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): generalized native compaction ownership for CLI backends",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nGeneralizes native-compaction ownership for CLI backends via a new `ownsNativeCompaction` capability flag.\n\nWhen a CLI backend runs an agent that compacts its **own** transcript (Claude Code's internal auto-compaction; Codex's app-server) and the session has **no** native-harness compaction endpoint, OpenClaw's CLI compaction lifecycle returns a **no-op** instead of running its safeguard summarizer — it defers to the backend rather than fighting the backend's own compaction or hard-failing the turn.\n\n- `claude-cli` / `claude-cli-interactive` declare `ownsNativeCompaction: true` — Claude Code compacts internally and exposes no harness endpoint, so the lifecycle returns a no-op.\n- Codex continues to route to its native-harness compaction endpoint (matched by the session's `agentHarnessId`); the no-op applies **only** when there is no harness endpoint.\n\n## What changed since the last review\n\nThis PR has been **reduced to purely the opt-out.** The earlier `contextTokens` cap-precedence change (letting an explicit configured cap win over the GA-1M default) has been **removed**: because these backends opt out of OpenClaw compaction, the context budget never drives compaction for them, so \"cap below the native window\" was solving a problem that no longer exists once the backend owns compaction.\n\nConsequences of the reduction:\n- `src/agents/context.ts` and `src/agents/context.test.ts` are now **byte-identical to base** — no change to GA-1M window behavior, and the existing GA-window tests pass untouched.\n- The net diff is exactly: the `ownsNativeCompaction` capability, the CLI compaction-lifecycle defer, the backend declarations, and docs.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `src/agents/command/cli-compaction.test.ts` (+215 lines) deterministically exercises the lifecycle:\n  - over-budget `claude-cli` session with `ownsNativeCompaction` + no harness endpoint → lifecycle returns a no-op (defers);\n  - native-harness sessions (`agentHarnessId` match, e.g. Codex) still route to the harness compaction endpoint;\n  - non-owning backends still run the safeguard summarizer.\n- `src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts` covers capability registration.\n- Affected suite green locally (140 tests).\n\n## On live proof\n\nThe defer path is covered deterministically by the unit tests above. A live over-budget capture on `claude-cli` is awkward to stage honestly: opus/sonnet GA models report a 1M-token window, so a real session is essentially never *organically* over OpenClaw's budget, and forcing the condition means lowering the budget via config — which drives the exact code path the unit tests already assert. Requesting that the unit + source evidence suffice in lieu of a live recording; happy to attach a redacted live capture if a maintainer still wants one.\n",
        "branch": "feat/generalized-native-compaction-ownership",
